{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'd like to start tonight by something completely different,"},{"time":4000,"text":"asking you to join me by stepping off the land"},{"time":8000,"text":"and jumping into the open ocean for a moment."},{"time":13000,"text":"90 percent of the living space on the planet is in the open ocean,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and it's where life -- the title of our seminar tonight -- it's where life began."},{"time":23000,"text":"And it's a lively and a lovely place,"},{"time":26000,"text":"but we're rapidly changing the oceans with our --"},{"time":30000,"text":"not only with our overfishing, our irresponsible fishing,"},{"time":35000,"text":"our adding of pollutants like fertilizer from our cropland,"},{"time":40000,"text":"but also, most recently, with climate change,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and Steve Schneider, I'm sure, will be going into greater detail on this."},{"time":45000,"text":"Now, as we continue to tinker with the oceans,"},{"time":48000,"text":"more and more reports are predicting that the kinds of seas that we're creating"},{"time":53000,"text":"will be conducive to low-energy type of animals, like jellyfish and bacteria."},{"time":58000,"text":"And this might be the kind of seas we're headed for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"Now jellyfish are strangely hypnotic and beautiful,"},{"time":65000,"text":"and you'll see lots of gorgeous ones at the aquarium on Friday,"},{"time":70000,"text":"but they sting like hell, and jellyfish sushi and sashimi"},{"time":75000,"text":"is just not going to fill you up."},{"time":77000,"text":"About 100 grams of jellyfish equals four calories."},{"time":82000,"text":"So it may be good for the waistline,"},{"time":84000,"text":"but it probably won't keep you satiated for very long."},{"time":87000,"text":"And a sea that's just filled and teeming with jellyfish"},{"time":92000,"text":"isn't very good for all the other creatures that live in the oceans,"},{"time":95000,"text":"that is, unless you eat jellyfish."},{"time":98000,"text":"And this is this voracious predator launching a sneak attack"},{"time":102000,"text":"on this poor little unsuspecting jellyfish there, a by-the-wind sailor."},{"time":106000,"text":"And that predator is the giant ocean sunfish, the Mola mola,"},{"time":112000,"text":"whose primary prey are jellyfish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"This animal is in \"The Guinness World Book of Records\""},{"time":117000,"text":"for being the world's heaviest bony fish."},{"time":119000,"text":"It reaches up to almost 5,000 pounds -- on a diet of jellyfish, primarily."},{"time":126000,"text":"And I think it's kind of a nice little cosmological convergence here"},{"time":130000,"text":"that the Mola mola -- its common name is sunfish --"},{"time":133000,"text":"that its favorite food is the moon jelly."},{"time":137000,"text":"So it's kind of nice, the sun and the moon getting together this way,"},{"time":141000,"text":"even if one is eating the other."},{"time":146000,"text":"Now this is typically how you see sunfish,"},{"time":149000,"text":"this is where they get their common name."},{"time":151000,"text":"They like to sunbathe, can't blame them."},{"time":153000,"text":"They just lay out on the surface of the sea"},{"time":156000,"text":"and most people think they're sick or lazy, but that's a typical behavior,"},{"time":160000,"text":"they lie out and bask on the surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"Their other name, Mola mola, is -- it sounds Hawaiian,"},{"time":166000,"text":"but it's actually Latin for millstone,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and that's attributable to their roundish, very bizarre, cut-off shape."},{"time":175000,"text":"It's as if, as they were growing, they just forgot the tail part."},{"time":179000,"text":"And that's actually what drew me to the Mola in the first place,"},{"time":183000,"text":"was this terribly bizarre shape."},{"time":186000,"text":"You know, you look at sharks, and they're streamlined, and they're sleek,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and you look at tuna, and they're like torpedoes --"},{"time":194000,"text":"they just give away their agenda. They're about migration and strength,"},{"time":198000,"text":"and then you look at the sunfish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"And this is just so elegantly mysterious, it's just --"},{"time":210000,"text":"it really kind of holds its cards a lot tighter than say, a tuna."},{"time":217000,"text":"So I was just intrigued with what -- you know, what is this animal's story?"},{"time":223000,"text":"Well, as with anything in biology, nothing really makes sense"},{"time":226000,"text":"except in the light of evolution."},{"time":228000,"text":"The Mola's no exception."},{"time":230000,"text":"They appeared shortly after the dinosaurs disappeared,"},{"time":234000,"text":"65 million years ago, at a time when whales still had legs,"},{"time":238000,"text":"and they come from a rebellious little puffer fish faction --"},{"time":244000,"text":"oblige me a little Kipling-esque storytelling here."},{"time":247000,"text":"Of course evolution is somewhat random, and you know,"},{"time":250000,"text":"about 55 million years ago there was this rebellious little puffer fish faction"},{"time":254000,"text":"that said, oh, the heck with the coral reefs --"},{"time":256000,"text":"we're going to head to the high seas."},{"time":258000,"text":"And lots of generations, lots of tweaking and torquing,"},{"time":263000,"text":"and we turn our puffer into the Mola."},{"time":265000,"text":"You know, if you give Mother Nature enough time, that is what she will produce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"They look -- maybe they look"},{"time":275000,"text":"kind of prehistoric and unfinished, abridged perhaps,"},{"time":279000,"text":"but in fact, in fact they are the --"},{"time":283000,"text":"they vie for the top position of the most evolutionarily-derived fish in the sea,"},{"time":289000,"text":"right up there with flat fish."},{"time":292000,"text":"They're -- every single thing about that fish has been changed."},{"time":296000,"text":"And in terms of fishes --"},{"time":298000,"text":"fishes appeared 500 million years ago, and they're pretty modern,"},{"time":304000,"text":"just 50 million years ago, so --"},{"time":308000,"text":"so interestingly, they give away their ancestry as they develop."},{"time":313000,"text":"They start as little eggs,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and they're in \"The Guinness World Book of Records\" again"},{"time":317000,"text":"for having the most number of eggs of any vertebrate on the planet."},{"time":321000,"text":"A single four-foot female had 300 million eggs,"},{"time":327000,"text":"can carry 300 million eggs in her ovaries -- imagine --"},{"time":330000,"text":"and they get to be over 10 feet long. Imagine what a 10 foot one has."},{"time":335000,"text":"And from that little egg,"},{"time":337000,"text":"they pass through this spiky little porcupine fish stage, reminiscent of their ancestry,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and develop -- this is their little adolescent stage."},{"time":345000,"text":"They school as adolescents, and become behemoth loners as adults."},{"time":352000,"text":"That's a little diver up there in the corner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"They're in \"The Guinness World Book of Records\" again"},{"time":358000,"text":"for being the vertebrate growth champion of the world."},{"time":361000,"text":"From their little hatching size of their egg, into their little larval stage"},{"time":365000,"text":"till they reach adulthood, they put on 600 million times an increase in weight."},{"time":371000,"text":"600 million. Now imagine if you gave birth to a little baby,"},{"time":377000,"text":"and you had to feed this thing."},{"time":381000,"text":"That would mean that your child, you would expect it to gain the weight of six Titanics."},{"time":388000,"text":"Now I don't know how you'd feed a child like that but --"},{"time":391000,"text":"we don't know how fast the Molas grow in the wild,"},{"time":397000,"text":"but captive growth studies at the Monterey Bay Aquarium --"},{"time":400000,"text":"one of the first places to have them in captivity --"},{"time":402000,"text":"they had one that gained 800 lbs in 14 months."},{"time":406000,"text":"I said, now, that's a true American."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"So being a loner is a great thing, especially in today's seas,"},{"time":419000,"text":"because schooling used to be salvation for fishes,"},{"time":422000,"text":"but it's suicide for fishes now."},{"time":425000,"text":"But unfortunately Molas, even though they don't school,"},{"time":427000,"text":"they still get caught in nets as by-catch."},{"time":429000,"text":"If we're going to save the world from total jellyfish domination,"},{"time":434000,"text":"then we've got to figure out what the jellyfish predators --"},{"time":436000,"text":"how they live their lives, like the Mola."},{"time":438000,"text":"And unfortunately, they make up a large portion of the California by-catch --"},{"time":443000,"text":"up to 26 percent of the drift net."},{"time":445000,"text":"And in the Mediterranean, in the swordfish net fisheries,"},{"time":450000,"text":"they make up up to 90 percent."},{"time":454000,"text":"So we've got to figure out how they're living their lives."},{"time":457000,"text":"And how do you do that?"},{"time":459000,"text":"How do you do that with an animal -- very few places in the world."},{"time":462000,"text":"This is an open ocean creature. It knows no boundaries -- it doesn't go to land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466000,"text":"How do you get insight?"},{"time":468000,"text":"How do you seduce an open ocean creature like that to spill its secrets?"},{"time":473000,"text":"Well, there's some great new technology"},{"time":476000,"text":"that has just recently become available,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and it's just a boon for getting insight into open ocean animals."},{"time":482000,"text":"And it's pictured right here, that little tag up there."},{"time":486000,"text":"That little tag can record temperature, depth and light intensity,"},{"time":491000,"text":"which is correlated with time, and from that we can get locations."},{"time":495000,"text":"And it can record this data for up to two years,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and keep it in that tag, release at a pre-programmed time,"},{"time":503000,"text":"float to the surface, upload all that data, that whole travelogue,"},{"time":507000,"text":"to satellite, which relays it directly to our computers,"},{"time":510000,"text":"and we've got that whole dataset. And we didn't even have --"},{"time":514000,"text":"we just had to tag the animal and then we went home and you know, sat at our desks."},{"time":519000,"text":"So the great thing about the Mola"},{"time":521000,"text":"is that when we put the tag on them -- if you look up here --"},{"time":524000,"text":"that's streaming off, that's right where we put the tag."},{"time":526000,"text":"And it just so happens that's a parasite hanging off the Mola."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"Molas are infamous for carrying tons of parasites."},{"time":533000,"text":"They're just parasite hotels; even their parasites have parasites."},{"time":537000,"text":"I think Donne wrote a poem about that."},{"time":539000,"text":"But they have 40 genera of parasites,"},{"time":542000,"text":"and so we figured just one more parasite won't be too much of a problem."},{"time":546000,"text":"And they happen to be a very good vehicle for carrying oceanographic equipment."},{"time":551000,"text":"They don't seem to mind, so far."},{"time":554000,"text":"So what are we trying to find out? We're focusing on the Pacific."},{"time":558000,"text":"We're tagging on the California coast, and we're tagging over in Taiwan and Japan."},{"time":562000,"text":"And we're interested in how these animals are using the currents,"},{"time":565000,"text":"using temperature, using the open ocean, to live their lives."},{"time":571000,"text":"We'd love to tag in Monterey."},{"time":573000,"text":"Monterey is one of the few places in the world where Molas come in large numbers."},{"time":577000,"text":"Not this time of year -- it's more around October."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"And we'd love to tag here -- this is an aerial shot of Monterey --"},{"time":583000,"text":"but unfortunately, the Molas here end up looking like this"},{"time":587000,"text":"because another one of our locals really likes Molas but in the wrong way."},{"time":591000,"text":"The California sea lion takes the Molas as soon as they come into the bay,"},{"time":595000,"text":"rips off their fins, fashions them into the ultimate Frisbee, Mola style,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and then tosses them back and forth."},{"time":602000,"text":"And I'm not exaggerating, it is just --"},{"time":605000,"text":"and sometimes they don't eat them, it's just spiteful."},{"time":608000,"text":"And you know, the locals think it's terrible behavior,"},{"time":613000,"text":"it's just horrible watching this happen, day after day."},{"time":618000,"text":"The poor little Molas coming in, getting ripped to shreds,"},{"time":621000,"text":"so we head down south, to San Diego."},{"time":625000,"text":"Not so many California sea lions down there."},{"time":627000,"text":"And the Molas there, you can find them with a spotter plane very easily,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and they like to hang out under floating rafts of kelp."},{"time":633000,"text":"And under those kelps -- this is why the Molas come there"},{"time":636000,"text":"because it's spa time for the Molas there."},{"time":640000,"text":"As soon as they get under those rafts of kelp, the exfoliating cleaner fish come."},{"time":644000,"text":"And they come and give the Molas --"},{"time":646000,"text":"you can see they strike this funny little position that says,"},{"time":649000,"text":"\"I'm not threatening, but I need a massage.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"And they'll put their fins out and their eyes go in the back of their head,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and the fish come up and they just clean, clean, clean --"},{"time":663000,"text":"because the Molas, you know, there's just a smorgasbord of parasites."},{"time":667000,"text":"And it's also a great place to go down south"},{"time":669000,"text":"because the water's warmer, and the Molas are kind of friendly down there."},{"time":673000,"text":"I mean what other kind of fish, if you approach it right,"},{"time":676000,"text":"will say, \"Okay, scratch me right there.\""},{"time":678000,"text":"You truly can swim up to a Mola -- they're very gentle --"},{"time":681000,"text":"and if you approach them right, you can give them a scratch and they enjoy it."},{"time":687000,"text":"So we've also tagged one part of the Pacific;"},{"time":689000,"text":"we've gone over to another part of the Pacific,"},{"time":691000,"text":"and we've tagged in Taiwan, and we tagged in Japan."},{"time":695000,"text":"And over in these places, the Molas are caught in set nets that line these countries."},{"time":700000,"text":"And they're not thrown back as by-catch, they're eaten."},{"time":703000,"text":"We were served a nine-course meal of Mola after we tagged."},{"time":708000,"text":"Well, not the one we tagged!"},{"time":711000,"text":"And everything from the kidney, to the testes, to the back bone,"},{"time":714000,"text":"to the fin muscle to -- I think that ís pretty much the whole fish -- is eaten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"So the hardest part of tagging, now, is"},{"time":731000,"text":"after you put that tag on, you have to wait, months."},{"time":736000,"text":"And you're just wondering, oh, I hope the fish is safe,"},{"time":740000,"text":"I hope, I hope it's going to be able to actually live its life out"},{"time":744000,"text":"during the course that the tag is recording."},{"time":747000,"text":"The tags cost 3500 dollars each, and then satellite time is another 500 dollars,"},{"time":753000,"text":"so you're like, oh, I hope the tag is okay."},{"time":756000,"text":"And so the waiting is really the hardest part."},{"time":759000,"text":"I'm going to show you our latest dataset."},{"time":761000,"text":"And it hasn't been published, so it's totally privy information just for TED."},{"time":766000,"text":"And in showing you this, you know, when we're looking at this data,"},{"time":770000,"text":"we're thinking, oh do these animals, do they cross the equator?"},{"time":773000,"text":"Do they go from one side of the Pacific to the other?"},{"time":775000,"text":"And we found that they kind of are homebodies."},{"time":780000,"text":"They're not big migrators. This is their track:"},{"time":782000,"text":"we deployed the tag off of Tokyo, and the Mola in one month"},{"time":786000,"text":"kind of got into the Kuroshio Current off of Japan and foraged there."},{"time":791000,"text":"And after four months, went up, you know, off of the north part of Japan."},{"time":795000,"text":"And that's kind of their home range."},{"time":797000,"text":"Now that's important, though, because if there's a lot of fishing pressure,"},{"time":801000,"text":"that population doesn't get replenished."},{"time":804000,"text":"So that's a very important piece of data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"But also what's important is that they're not slacker, lazy fish."},{"time":812000,"text":"They're super industrious."},{"time":814000,"text":"And this is a day in the life of a Mola, and if we --"},{"time":817000,"text":"they're up and down, and up and down, and up and down, and up"},{"time":821000,"text":"and up and down, up to 40 times a day."},{"time":823000,"text":"As the sun comes up, you see in the blue, they start their dive."},{"time":828000,"text":"Down -- and as the sun gets brighter they go a little deeper, little deeper."},{"time":832000,"text":"They plumb the depths down to 600 meters, in temperatures to one degree centigrade,"},{"time":838000,"text":"and this is why you see them on the surface -- it's so cold down there."},{"time":842000,"text":"They've got to come up, warm, get that solar power,"},{"time":844000,"text":"and then plunge back into the depths, and go up and down and up and down."},{"time":847000,"text":"And they're hitting a layer down there; it's called the deep scattering layer --"},{"time":850000,"text":"which a whole variety of food's in that layer."},{"time":855000,"text":"So rather than just being some sunbathing slacker,"},{"time":859000,"text":"they're really very industrious fish that dance this wild dance"},{"time":862000,"text":"between the surface and the bottom and through temperature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"We see the same pattern -- now with these tags"},{"time":870000,"text":"we're seeing a similar pattern for swordfishes, manta rays, tunas,"},{"time":874000,"text":"a real three-dimensional play."},{"time":879000,"text":"This is part of a much larger program called the Census of Marine Life,"},{"time":882000,"text":"where they're going to be tagging all over the world"},{"time":885000,"text":"and the Mola's going to enter into that."},{"time":887000,"text":"And what's exciting -- you all travel, and you know"},{"time":890000,"text":"the best thing about traveling is to be able to find the locals,"},{"time":893000,"text":"and to find the great places by getting the local knowledge."},{"time":896000,"text":"Well now with the Census of Marine Life, we'll be able to sidle up to all the locals"},{"time":900000,"text":"and explore 90 percent of our living space, with local knowledge."},{"time":905000,"text":"It's never -- it's really never been a more exciting, or a vital time, to be a biologist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911000,"text":"Which brings me to my last point, and what I think is kind of the most fun."},{"time":915000,"text":"I set up a website because I was getting so many questions about Molas and sunfish."},{"time":923000,"text":"And so I just figured I'd have the questions answered,"},{"time":927000,"text":"and I'd be able to thank my funders, like National Geographic and Lindbergh."},{"time":931000,"text":"But people would write into the site with all sorts of,"},{"time":935000,"text":"all sorts of stories about these animals"},{"time":938000,"text":"and wanting to help me get samples for genetic analysis."},{"time":942000,"text":"And what I found most exciting is that everyone had a shared --"},{"time":949000,"text":"a shared love and an interest in the oceans."},{"time":952000,"text":"I was getting reports from Catholic nuns,"},{"time":956000,"text":"Jewish Rabbis, Muslims, Christians -- everybody writing in,"},{"time":961000,"text":"united by their love of life."},{"time":965000,"text":"And to me that -- I don't think I could say it any better than the immortal Bard himself:"},{"time":971000,"text":"\"One touch of nature makes the whole world kin.\""},{"time":975000,"text":"And sure, it may be just one big old silly fish, but it's helping."},{"time":979000,"text":"If it's helping to unite the world, I think it's definitely the fish of the future."}]}]}